50|$|Sodium {{hexametaphosphate}} (SHMP) is a hexamer {{of composition}} (NaPO3)6. Sodium hexametaphosphate of commerce is typically {{a mixture of}} polymeric metaphosphates, of which the hexamer is one, and is usually the compound referred to by this name. It is more correctly termed <b>sodium</b> <b>polymetaphosphate.</b>|$|E

